PortalBehavior
public class ISPServiceBehavior
extends GenericPortalBehavior

Implementation of the "ISP Service Behavior" (previously known as "Normal Behavior".

The ISP Service Behavior allows users to activate and deactivate their services. It does not provide any special functionality for users connected through DHCP. I.e. the portal does not provide any functionality to switch IP addresses obtained through DHCP.
